Pleased I turned down the option to over book myself for lessons on Sunday, had someone calling up asking for a Level 1 lesson and when they asked me why I wouldn't do it, I said I already had 5 hours of lessons on Sunday and offered them Monday.

Had a nice sleep, from around 1.30am to 10.00am. Woke up by my partner with a coffee. Made breakfast for us both. Ate breakfast watching Homes under the Hammer. Checked bank balances. Got a lesson at 1.30pm and maybe again at 3.30pm.

Had a Level 1 kitesurfing lesson on the beach with a completely new customer. I was rushing to get there and was slightly late (5 min), but messaged in advance and he said no worries. There was going to be the option to do the Level 2 in the water afterwards, but the wind wasn't strong enough and I wasn't feeling enthusiastic about teaching in the water anyway, so was relieved. Afterwards I had an iced coffee and a panini. Feeling quite sleepy now. It's been quite warm today in the sunshine, which has been nice. Seda asked for a lift from the shop later, there is stuff to carry and also I think her back is hurting.

Not feeling sleepy any more. Think maybe refined white bread makes me feel sleepy. Feeling quite chirpy after some banter on a group chat on WhatsApp. Seda has gone for a drink and to hang out with Josh, so having some evening time on my own.

I'm deciding whether to teach a Level 2 lessons at 3.30pm today, the weather is rainy and miserable compared to yesterday and the wind is a bit light, but I should go and try and run the lesson really, although the guy is travelling from London, so I don't want him to have a wasted journey. I said I will decide by 2pm. Slept well and breakfast was healthy . Will probably be more cheerful after I make a decision about this lesson!

I always feel better after teaching in the water, even though I really didn't feel like it today. Student made good progress. Wind was good and it wasn't raining after all during the lesson. Few kites out at Lancing, but none of the East Worthing crew came down. Looking similar for tomorrow with the same student, similar wind conditions, but sunny and warm. Feeling nice after warming up in a hot shower too.

Slept for a long time last night. Fell asleep watching a film 11pm, then went to bed 12pm and was hard to wake up even at 10.15am even when my partner woke me. Probably just tired from teaching kitesurfing in the water as it's quite physical as you are walking through the water quite a lot.

I've been working on my lap top during the day. Eventually decided there wasn't enough wind for the Level 3 lesson. Rearranged it for tomorrow. Went for a very pleasant bike ride along Brighton seafront. Went to help at the shop a bit by giving Seda a loo break and stayed a bit while she was serving customers. Just had a glass of wine, no phone, no screen and continued reading my book Think and Grow Rich, by Napoleon Hill. I undoubtedly feel good or better when I don't look at my phone and do things like read interesting books. However I don't make time to do this very often. I rarely read books even though I find it enriching and rewarding to do so.

I find I'm very sensitive to communications from students or customers at the moment. I find their tone can put me in a bad mood, even though it's probably nothing personal. I've been trying to sell my kitesurfing business as I don't want to do this forever and that makes me feel a bit negative as I didn't have a successful experience selling it with Knightsbridge PLC. I think I have to try and stay positive because selling a niche business is about finding the right fit of buyer I think. You have to be quite patient. I'm also finding it quite frustrating as I want to have more instructors and haven't been able to recruit any yet this year.

Cancelled the lesson due to lack of wind. Made a nice tray bake dinner for my partner and I. Feeling especially valued by my partner as she is saying nice things to me such as you are the best fiance, you are the cutest fiance. Talked over dinner. Am driving her to the airport tomorrow. She is in Turkey for 9 days.

Watched my friend in her heat in the Aloha Classic 2022, which is a windsurfing wave sailing event with all the top competitors, from October 2022. She is 53 years old and she was ripping, she looked really good on her wave tides. So that is pretty inspirational. I find myself from time to time concerned about my age, that I'm nearly 50, about what does life mean and what will my legacy be. It's great to see female athletes performing so well in an open class against all ages. I'm giving Seda a lift to Stansted today, I like driving and am confident driving, but always gets slightly anxious about making her flight time, we are setting off in plenty of time though. Busy day as I also have a kitesurfing lesson at 5pm later.

Riccardo my instructor is running my Level 2 kitesurfing lesson, while he runs it I went for a short walk/run and some body weight exercises to check my hamstring recovery. Felt pretty good  .  Dropped Seda at the airport, Stansted, just after 12pm, all went fine, goodbye was a bit rushed as the bus driver was hurrying her to get on the bus. She has already landed and her brother is about to pick her up from the airport. I'm happy she had a safe flight and will spend some nice time with her Mum and brother. I would go and visit my parents this week, but unfortunately they are in Cornwall, but if the wind is no good for kitesurfing lessons I may take a road trip down there :)

Feeling quite positive today. Went to bed late (as get quite scared staying on my own), but slept very well. Had a couple of useful conversations around business today, one about valuing and selling my business and one with the kite school next door to me, just had a bit of a gossip about the Council and Worthing Beach really. Phone calls are more rewarding than email or message I think.

Went to a different evening of touch with a new group called Brighton Serpents at Hove RFC. They were extremely friendly and welcoming. At least 7 people introduced themselves to me as they could see I was new. Was a nice fun, not too strenuous session, which is what I wanted physically too to see if my hamstring was feeling OK and it felt fine. If anything achilles was the thing I noticed hurting a little.

Slept quite a long time this morning, until 10.30am. Feeling optimistic about the day, got a list of things I want to get done this week and while Seda is away. Some household things and some work things.

Been resolving a warranty return and am irriated by the latest email from the warranty team at ION, which says I should send my spare part and then ask if the customer is happy with it, meaning I take the financial risk by sending my item from stock (last part is my interpretation). However I think it might just be the wording, I spoke to the other rep and he said don't worry we'll make sure you get a credit note for your spare part.

relaxing with my parents in Whitchurch again. Saw my friend Anna last night and had a good catch up

Picked Seda up from the airport last night. She was pretty tired and a bit grumpy after the flight. She is much more cheerful this morning and being much more loving pleasant and attentive.
Have enjoyed working in Yzill today with Seda :). Got a touch competition in Oxford tomorrow which am looking forward to.

Played in a national development comp yesterday with Surrey Bisons. Really fun day overall. Nice team, lots of young players with potential and some old wise heads too. Felt fit and good for the whole day, only started to feel a bit tired on the last game of the day. They were 20 minute games and we played 4 X pool games and then 2 further games (5th 6th play off, then 7th 8th play off), we had lots of good competitive games and weren't thrashed by any teams, I think biggest score was 4 1 to eventual winners. We won the last game by drop off to finish 7th over all. Not sure if I can make the next one unfortunately as getting in to high season for my business.

Drove to Greatstone two and half hours away in way there for kitesurfing lesson yesterday. Woke up yesterday feeling not good at all, as in tired, so was a long day with a long journey to start. Lesson was good though with one of my favourite students, a 76 year old with incredible zest for life. Feeling run down today, sinus feels a little sore, on verge of getting a chill or cold.

I tweaked my achilles a little last Weds, so have been icing that initially and now will go back on to isometric stretching. Got a few lessons organised in New Romney next week, looks like good conditions, if I get enough lessons I'm considering staying over at New Romney caravan park
This week been driving to New Romney for kitesurfing lessons every other day. Have had fabulous conditions over there. Feels like being on holiday going there, warm, sandy beach and windy
